cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses machine learning techniques such as support vector machines and optimization methods, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of circulant matrices and Fourier transforms indicates that it could be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as well.
